wiki.summary: “You Better Move” is the fifth track on Lil Uzi Vert’s second studio album Eternal Atake. The song prominently samples a sound effect from Space Cadet Pinball, and features lyrics surrounding nostalgia from Uzi’s childhood. The song’s video game sample could be seen as a homage to American rapper Spaceghostpurrp, who had previously sampled the videogame on his song “Friday,” and was featured on Uzi’s 2013 track “White Shit.” “You Better Move” debuted at #36 on the Billboard Hot 100 for the chart week of March 21, 2020. Read more on Last.fm.
